---
title: Rosemary Apricot Chicken with Garlicky Brussels Sprout & Onion Jumble
description: Friends, these are not your average, everyday pork chops. Our chefs have given them a restaurant-worthy makeover! The chops are coated in rosemary and garlic, and then seared to perfection. You’ll spoon a buttery, sweet, and tangy balsamic-apricot pan sauce over the top just before serving. The sides are just as satisfying—roasted, caramelized onion wedges and Brussels sprouts (who needs taters?) round everything out. It’s the savory, hearty 35-minute dinner idea you’ve been craving!
